1 unit(s) Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Lime
225 grams King Prawns
125 grams Egg Noodle Nest
80 grams Sugar Snap Peas
100 grams Bulgogi Sauce
25 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce

Boil a full kettle. Pour it into a saucepan with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.
Slice the pepper into strips.
Cut the lime into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat. Drain the prawns.
Once hot, fry the prawns, 2-3 mins. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're opaque in the middle.
Meanwhile, boil the noodles, 3-4 mins.
Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Next, add the pepper and sugar snap peas to the pan. Fry, 3-4 mins.
Stir in the bulgogi and soy. Cook, 1-2 mins. IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.
Add the cooked noodles to the pan. Toss to coat and warm through, 1-2 mins.
Add a splash of water if it's a bit dry.

Share the noodles between your bowls.
Serve with a lime wedge on the side for squeezing over.
Enjoy!